SALMONELLOSIS - UK (SCOTLAND)
*****************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.healthnet.org/programs/promed.html>
Date: Thu, 12 Nov 1998 03:24:54 -0500
Source: PA News, 11 Nov 1998 and FSNET
Via: Robert A. LaBudde <ral@lcfltd.com>

Health officials were cited as saying today that a third ex-serviceman,
aged 78, has died from [salmonellosis] at the Erskine Hospital for
ex-servicemen near Glasgow. Two other ex-servicemen at the hospital died on
October 31. More than 300 people have now been tested for the [organism],
and 29 have been confirmed as positive, including the man who died today.
--
ProMED-mail
e-mail: promed@usa.healthnet.org
[This report is fragmentary. It would be nice to know which _Salmonella_
strain we were dealing with here. One might also expect some official
speculation about probable common sources. Anyone having additional
information, please forward it to promed@usa.healthnet.org. - Mod.ES]
